Durban - A Durban family is counting up the costs after a fire ripped through their home on Thursday morning. Crisis Medical spokesperson, Kyle van Reenen, said they were alerted to reports of a house on fire in Jain Road, Kenville, before 8am. “Initial reports received from concerned neighbours stated that there were children in the house at the time. The necessary emergency personnel were also called to the scene. Fortunately, when we arrived at the house, we found that there were no children inside,” van Reenen said. He added that no injuries were reported and the cause of the fire is yet to be determined. "I would like to thank eThekwini Fire and Rescue Services for their swift response and action in fighting the blaze and to Busamed Gateway Private Hospital for being on standby should there have been any injuries," he said. Police and officials from eThekwini Fire Department would be investigating further. Daily News  